        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-2724",
        "content": "The judge, hearing these words, and being much incensed, ordered this holy confessor of God to be scourged by the executioners, believing that he might by stripes shake that constancy of heart, on which he could not prevail by words.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-normal_e-normal",
